  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The team I happened to bump into in a small town called Nova Lehota, which is about 15 kilometers southeast of Trencin, was a team that was headed by a professionally trained partisan who had previously been head of a partisan unit.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was an expert, what's called a [NON-ENGLISH], somebody-- a mining expert.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The team, at the time when I joined, it had about eight, eight members.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was only one other Russian.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Two other members were people who were communists.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "One of them, the older man, he was in his 40s.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was a man who actually fought in the International Brigade in Spain, and he brought his son, 18-year-old son.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was-- His name was Tatko.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "His codename was Tatko, and he immediately took possession of the light machine gun.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Then we had a young Czech refugee who escaped a camp, a prisoner camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "We had a young Ukrainian, also an escapee from a military transport of prisoners, Russian prisoners.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And all of these were totally strange to, to Trencin.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they sort of questioned me, what I did and how I got around.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And after telling my story, they said, well, you are just the kid we would like to have to walk ahead of the squad.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The mission of that squad was to intercept a single rail line.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The strategic position in the-- late in 1944 was that it wasn't clear yet whether the main attack of the Russians will come through the [?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Vistula ?] or through the Danube Basin.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And therefore the German High Command placed their reserves in a mobile status to be able to shuttle them across the Carpathian Mountains, which run east-west.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
